        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 5:14PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Wayside, or 19 miles north of Tulia, moving north at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Canyon, Clarendon, Howardwick, Buffalo Lake, Wayside, Palo Duro
Canyon, Greenbelt Lake, and Goodnight.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
